







       A CheckButton should be used to set options in the applica-
       tion.  A CheckButton is a special case of a ToggleButton.
       Any number of CheckButtons can be set at the same time.

       This component must be composed of a text or graphic label,
       and a graphic that indicates the state of the CheckButton.
       The graphic should be a square preceding the label, and
       should have two distinctive states indicating the set and
       unset states of the CheckButton.  On color systems, the on
       state color can be distinct from general application colors
       to visually distinguish the on state.







       CheckButtons must have no internal navigation.  The follow-
       ing text describes the CheckButton operations.

