                 Must arm the CheckButton.  If the CheckButton was
                 previously unset, it must show the CheckButton in
                 the set state.  If the CheckButton was previously
                 set, it must show the CheckButton in the unset
                 state.

       BBBBSSSSeeeelllleeeecccctttt RRRReeeelllleeeeaaaasssseeee:
                 If the release happens in the same CheckButton
                 that the press occurred in, then if the CheckBut-
                 ton was previously unset, it must be set, or if
                 the CheckButton was previously set, it must be
                 unset.  In all cases the CheckButton must be
                 disarmed, and if the CheckButton was in a Menu,
                 the Menu must be unposted.

       KKKKAAAAccccttttiiiivvvvaaaatttteeee: If the CheckButton was previously unset, it must
                 be set.  If the CheckButton was previously set, it
                 must be unset.  In both cases the CheckButton must
                 be disarmed, and if the CheckButton was in a Menu,
                 the Menu must be unposted.

       KKKKSSSSeeeelllleeeecccctttt:  If the CheckButton was previously unset, it must
                 be set.  If the CheckButton was previously set, it
                 must be unset.  In both cases the CheckButton must
                 be disarmed, and if the CheckButton was in a Menu,
                 the Menu must be unposted.

















